## 🚀 Getting Started (Local Development)

Before starting the Quarkus server, ensure that all background microservices and databases are running in the `Digital_Assistant_microServices` project.

### Pre-flight Check
To ensure proper connectivity and configuration (DB credentials, Keycloak OIDC, etc.), use the provided pre-flight script. This script verifies infrastructure health and starts the application only if all checks pass.

```bash
# From the Digital-Assistant-Server directory
./pre-flight-check.sh
```

The script will:
1. Check if all required Docker containers are running.
2. Verify MariaDB & Postgres connectivity using credentials from `DOCKER_MAP.md`.
3. Validate Keycloak OIDC configuration (Discovery & Token Grant).
4. Check Elasticsearch and NestJS API health.
5. Start the Quarkus application in dev mode (`./gradlew quarkusDev`).

---
Note that you will need both the server (this repo) and client (https://github.com/Digital-Assistant/Digital_Assistant_Client) to get the functionality in above video.
Will try to release a docker version of server soon to ease deployment.
